               <p>On the 6th of May, at about nine o'clock at night, as I was going along the street, I felt something at my pocket; I turned, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief; he put it behind him. I secured the handkerchief; he ran off, and I pursued, and took him.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I am not guilty.</p>
